# Mintlify component enforcement

When creating or updating any `.mdx` file, you MUST use Mintlify components instead of plain markdown equivalents. Plain markdown workarounds are not acceptable when a purpose-built component exists.

## Mandatory component substitutions

Before finishing any `.mdx` file edit, verify every item in this table:

| Plain markdown pattern | Required Mintlify component | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| `> **Note:**` or `> **Important:**` blockquotes | `<Note>`, `<Warning>`, `<Info>`, `<Tip>`, `<Check>` | Any callout, aside, or highlighted information |
| Manual "Step 1", "Step 2" headings or numbered procedures | `<Steps>` with `<Step title="...">` | Any sequential procedure (3+ steps) |
| Repeated code blocks showing alternatives | `<Tabs>` with `<Tab title="...">` | Alternative approaches, platform variants, or entity comparisons |
| Multiple sequential code blocks for the same concept | `<CodeGroup>` | Same logic in different languages or DTO variants |
| Long reference sections, checklists, or optional details | `<AccordionGroup>` with `<Accordion>` | Content readers may want to skip or scan selectively |
| Bullet-list of links at the end of a page | `<CardGroup>` with `<Card icon="..." href="...">` | Related documentation, next steps, or see-also sections |
| Manual table of contents | **Delete it** | Mintlify auto-generates sidebar TOC from headings |
| `> **Version:**` or metadata blockquotes | `<Info>` | Version, status, or endpoint metadata |
| "Do this / Don't do this" code comparisons | `<Tip>` for the good pattern, `<Warning>` for the anti-pattern | Performance patterns, best practices |

## Callout severity guide

Pick the correct callout based on severity:

| Component | Use for | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `<Note>` | Supplementary context safe to skip | "A user may have multiple stakeholder rows..." |
| `<Info>` | Neutral metadata or announcements | "Endpoint: POST /leads | Status: Implemented" |
| `<Tip>` | Best practices, recommended approaches | "Use optimized bulk methods for list views" |
| `<Warning>` | Destructive actions, breaking patterns, critical gotchas | "Never loop over individual permission computations" |
| `<Check>` | Success confirmation, verification steps | "Migration complete — verify by running..." |

## Heading case

Use **sentence case** for all headings: "Core concepts", not "Core Concepts".

## Pre-completion checklist

Before considering any `.mdx` edit done, verify:

- [ ] No `> **Note/Warning/Important**` blockquotes remain — replaced with callout components
- [ ] No manual table of contents — Mintlify generates this automatically
- [ ] Sequential procedures use `<Steps>` / `<Step>`
- [ ] Alternative content (variants, comparisons) uses `<Tabs>` / `<Tab>`
- [ ] Related code variants use `<CodeGroup>`
- [ ] Long optional/reference sections use `<AccordionGroup>` / `<Accordion>`
- [ ] "Related documentation" or "See also" links use `<CardGroup>` / `<Card>`
- [ ] All headings use sentence case
- [ ] Frontmatter includes both `title` and `description`
- [ ] All code blocks have language tags
